{"word":"Hoshea","slug":"hoshea","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>Hoshea</b> <a href=\"#/H1954\">H1954</a> <br/> 1. Called also Oshea, the original name of Joshua<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=4&chapter=13&verse=8'>Num 13:8</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=4&chapter=13&verse=16'>Num 13:16</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=5&chapter=32&verse=44'>Deu 32:44</a><br/> 2. A chief of Ephraim<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=27&verse=20'>1Ch 27:20</a><br/> 3. King of Israel:<br/> - Assassinates Pekah and usurps the throne<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=15&verse=30'>2Ki 15:30</a> <br/> - Evil reign of<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=17&verse=2'>2Ki 17:2</a> <br/> - Becomes subject to Assyria<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=17&verse=3'>2Ki 17:3</a> <br/> - Conspires against Assyria and is imprisoned<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=17&verse=4'>2Ki 17:4</a> <br/> - Last king of Israel<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=17&verse=6'>2Ki 17:6</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=18&verse=12'>2Ki 18:12</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=28&chapter=10&verse=3'>Hos 10:3</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=28&chapter=10&verse=7'>Hos 10:7</a> <br/> 4. A Jewish exile<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=16&chapter=10&verse=23'>Neh 10:23</a>"}]}